# PATIENT APP

*Every feature is designed to collect structured clinical data, maximize engagement through gamification, and sync to the provider dashboard in real time. No billing is processed through the platform — all data is exported to EMR/Kipu for billing workflows.*

## Recovery Counter & Home Dashboard

- Days clean counter with real-time tracking

- Hours in recovery, estimated money saved, health improvement percentage

- Streak tracking (daily, weekly, milestone-based)

- Level badge and XP balance in persistent header (tappable to Rewards)

- Milestone share card — share achievements with family, sponsor, and care team

- AI smart nudge — predicts peak craving windows and surfaces proactively on home screen

## MAT Medication Tracker

- Current medication display: drug name, dosage, formulation, prescriber, schedule

- Supports Suboxone, Methadone, and Naltrexone (oral and injectable)

- One-tap dose confirmation with XP reward (+50 XP)

- "Remind Later" snooze option

- Weekly adherence calendar — visual M/T/W/Th/F/S/S grid with done/due/pending states

- Running adherence streak counter (e.g., “47-day streak · 100%”)

- Side effects check — selectable tags: None, Headache, Nausea, Constipation, Drowsiness, Sweating

- Pharmacy refill tracker — next refill date, pharmacy name and location

- All MAT data syncs to provider dashboard in real time

## Craving & Mood Tracking

- Real-time craving slider (0–10 scale) on home screen

- Dynamic color coding — green (low), gold (moderate), red (high)

- Auto-triggered alert at craving ≥ 7 — links directly to Urge Support

- Daily check-in screen with mood selector (emoji-based: Rough, Okay, Good, Great)

- Craving, pain, and sleep quality sliders within check-in

- Trigger selection tags: Stress, Pain, Boredom, Social, Financial, None

- Submit with XP reward (+30 XP) — all check-in data syncs to provider in real time

## COWS Withdrawal Tracker

- Clinical Opiate Withdrawal Scale (COWS) assessment

- Current score display with severity label (Minimal, Mild, Moderate, Severe)

- Symptom-by-symptom rating: muscle/bone aches, anxiety/irritability, insomnia, cravings

- Visual progress bars per symptom

- Submit to Care Team button with XP reward (+35 XP)

- Score syncs to provider dashboard for withdrawal trajectory monitoring

## Pain Management Tools

- Educational context: “Chronic pain is the #1 trigger for opioid relapse”

- Non-opioid strategy library: Heat/Cold Therapy, Mindfulness for Pain, Gentle Movement, CBT for Chronic Pain

- XP reward for using pain tools (+20 XP)

- Pain data syncs to provider for pain-craving correlation analytics

## Sage AI Companion

- OUD-trained AI recovery companion available 24/7

- Multi-language support (10+ languages)

- Full conversational chat interface with message bubbles

- Quick-action suggestion chips: non-opioid pain tips, craving plans, care team contact

- Covers: craving intervention, pain management coaching, MAT education, relapse prevention, emotional support

- XP reward per session (+15 XP)

- Chat sentiment data analyzed via NLP and shared with provider (never raw transcripts)

## Urge Support Mode

- Activated manually or auto triggered at craving ≥ 7

- Reassurance messaging with urge duration education (15–20 min average)

- Animated guided breathing exercise (4-count visualization)

- Quick-action crisis tools: call sponsor, Sage AI, grounding exercise (5-4-3-2-1), family reward anchor

- Urge mode activation data tracked and synced to provider

## Relapse Support Mode

- Compassionate, non-judgmental interface: “This is not the end”

- Action options: Call 911, report to care team (confidential), Sage AI, locate Narcan

- XP, achievements, and family rewards are preserved after relapse

- Relapse events logged and synced to provider with AI alert

## Crisis / SOS Support

- Persistent SOS floating action button visible on all screens

- Emergency hotlines with tap-to-call: 911, 988, SAMHSA (1-800-662-4357), Crisis Text Line

- Full care team contacts with individual Call and Text buttons:

- MAT Prescriber (Dr. Rivera)

- Therapist (Dr. Chen)

- Sponsor (Mike R.)

- Emergency Contact / Family Member (Mom)

- Care team notified when SOS is accessed

## Voice Journal

- Audio recording interface with tap-to-record

- AI-powered mood and sentiment analysis (NLP)

- Recent entries log with date, duration, and detected mood

- Privacy: words analyzed for mood patterns — never raw audio

- XP reward per entry (+25 XP)

- Strongest early relapse predictor: detects mood decline 5–7 days before events

## Sleep & Recovery Log

- Summary: hours slept, quality rating, logging streak

- Sleep data correlated with morning craving levels

- Educational framing: “Poor sleep amplifies cravings”

- XP reward (+20 XP) — data syncs to provider

## Body Recovery Timeline

- Visual timeline of physical healing at current clean day count

- Stages: Acute Withdrawal (Wk 1–2), GI Healing (Wk 3–4), Endorphin Restoration (Wk 5–8), Sleep/Mood Normalization (Mo 3+), Brain Receptor Healing (Mo 6+)

- Done/Now/Upcoming status indicators with progress bars

## CBT & Digital Therapeutics

- Prescribed Digital Therapeutic: CBT for Substance Use (CBT4SUD)

- 8-module structured program with progress tracking and completion percentage

- Module library: Understanding OUD, MAT as Your Ally, Opioid Trigger Map, Pain Without Opioids, Rebuilding Relationships, Understanding Relapse

- Done/Now/Next/Locked states with lesson counts per module

- XP reward per session (+75 XP) and per lesson (+15 XP)

- Session data generates documentation for EMR billing codes (H2019, G2213/G2214)

## Naloxone (Narcan) Hub

- Narcan kit inventory: dose count, formulation, expiration date

- Family training status per family member

- OD response plan — step-by-step guide

- Find Free Narcan Near Me — pharmacies, health departments, community organizations

- Fentanyl safety education — test strips, harm reduction

- Narcan status syncs to provider Narcan Network dashboard

## SDOH Monthly Wellness Screener

- Social Determinants of Health screening: housing, food, transportation, social support

- Simple response options per question

- XP reward (+40 XP)

- Responses generate Z-code documentation for EMR export (enables higher E/M billing)

## Appointments & Attendance

- Today’s schedule with color-coded types: MAT Clinic, Therapy, NA Meeting, Drug Court

- Per-appointment “Confirm Attended” button with XP reward (+25 XP)

- Upcoming appointments section

- Attendance data syncs to provider dashboard

## Drug Screen Tracker

- UDS compliance dashboard with running completion rate and streak

- Upcoming drug screen schedule with date, type (random/scheduled), and location

- Confirm Screen Completed button with XP reward (+30 XP)

- Recent results history with expected medication detection

- Overdue screen alert with push notification

- All UDS data syncs to provider for G0480-G0483 toxicology documentation

- Results feed into AI relapse risk scoring and MAT adherence correlation

## Group Session Check-In

- Weekly group session schedule with session name, time, and facilitator

- One-tap attendance confirmation with XP reward (+25 XP)

- Session types: Relapse Prevention, MAT Education, CBT Skills, Pain &amp; Recovery, Peer Support

- Monthly attendance stats and session duration tracking

- Supports H0005/90853 group therapy and H2019 DTx billing documentation

- AI correlates group attendance with relapse risk and engagement scores

## Post-Discharge Transition Support (TCM)

- Activates automatically when patient transitions between levels of care

- Transition status display: Day X of 30, origin and destination level of care

- TCM checklist: 2-day contact, medication reconciliation, face-to-face visit, 30-day follow-through

- Auto-captures 2-day post-discharge contact via app check-in

- Medication reconciliation confirmation against discharge orders

- Daily transition check-in with adjustment status and medication compliance

- Supports 99495 ($201) and 99496 ($273) TCM billing codes

- Post-discharge daily check earns XP (+20 XP)

- Transition Mode auto-triggered when discharge data syncs from Kipu EMR

## Functional Status Assessment

- Monthly check covering employment, daily living, and social support

- Employment tracking: Full-time, Part-time, Seeking, Not able

- Daily living assessment and social support strength rating

- Supports CCM (99490) documentation and continued care authorization

- Functional improvement trends support outcomes reporting to payers

- XP reward for completion (+35 XP)

## SBIRT Screening (Substance Use Risk Screen)

- DAST-10 based validated substance use disorder risk screening tool

- Completed annually or when transitioning between levels of care

- Scoring with severity categorization: Low, Moderate, Substantial, Severe

- Supports 99408 ($34) and 99409 ($67) SBIRT billing codes

- XP reward for completion (+40 XP)

- Data feeds into AI risk scoring and treatment outcome tracking

## Naloxone Dispensing Documentation (G2216)

- Take-home naloxone supply tracking: doses received, date, product type

- Family training completion status per household member

- Expiration monitoring with replacement reminders

- Supports G2216 billing code (~$19 per dispensing)

- Integrated within Narcan Hub alongside OD Response Plan and Narcan locator

## Notifications Center

- MAT dose reminders with XP incentive

- Family reward notifications (“Mom added a new reward!”)

- AI craving window predictions

- Care team messages

## Profile

- User avatar, name, clean date, current level and XP

- Current medication and prescriber

- Care team listing: MAT Prescriber, Therapist, Sponsor

- Connected family members with reward pledge counts

- Settings, preferences, and privacy/data sharing controls

# GAMIFICATION & FAMILY REWARDS SYSTEM

*The gamification system is the primary engagement driver. Every XP-earning action directly generates structured clinical data for provider reporting and EMR billing code eligibility. Patients with active family rewards show 4.2× better retention and 34% lower relapse rates.*

## XP Points System

Every data-generating action earns XP:

| **Action** | **XP Earned** |
| --- | --- |
| Log MAT medication | **+50** |
| Complete daily check-in | **+30** |
| Complete CBT/DTx session | **+75** |
| Voice journal entry | **+25** |
| Log sleep | **+20** |
| Submit COWS assessment | **+35** |
| Sage AI conversation | **+15** |
| Use pain management tool | **+20** |
| Complete monthly SDOH screener | **+40** |
| Confirm appointment attended | **+25** |
| Complete workbook lesson | **+15** |

## Level Progression System

6-level system with recovery-themed names:

| **Level** | **Name** | **XP Threshold** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **L1** | Seed | 0 |
| **L2** | Sprout | 500 |
| **L3** | Root | 1,200 |
| **L4** | Bloom | 2,000 |
| **L5** | Flourish | 3,000 |
| **L6** | Thrive | 5,000 |

## Family Reward Board

- Family members pledge real-world incentives tied to recovery milestones

- Reward types: gift cards, meals/dinners, experiences (movie night, fishing trip), trips

- Visual progress bar per reward showing completion percentage

- Milestone triggers: day count targets, level targets, streak targets

- “Earned” badge for claimed rewards

- Family reward reminders surface in Urge Mode as coping anchors

- Family members receive milestone notifications

## Achievements & Streaks

- Unlockable achievement badges: 30 Day Hero, MAT Master, Sage Friend, and more

- Badge grid in Rewards screen

- Daily streak counter in recovery counter and MAT tracker

- Weekly adherence calendar with visual M–S progress

## Recovery Flame (Streak Visualization)

*Leverages loss aversion psychology — people fear losing something 2× more than they enjoy gaining it. The Recovery Flame replaces the static streak counter with a living, animated visual element that patients feel compelled to protect.*

- Animated flame icon replaces static streak counter — grows larger and changes color with streak length

- Flame color tiers: Blue Flame (7 days), Purple Flame (30 days), Gold Flame (90 days), Platinum Flame (180 days), Diamond Flame (365 days)

- Flame starts flickering if patient misses a day — push notification: “Your 47-day Recovery Flame is fading. Open VictoryAI to keep it alive.”

- 4-hour grace window before flame tier drops (flame drops one tier but never fully resets — compassionate for recovery population)

- Flame visible on Home screen, Rewards screen, and Recovery Ring peer profiles

- Flame status syncs to provider Engagement & Gamification analytics dashboard

## Streak Shields

- One free Streak Shield per week — auto-protects the Recovery Flame if patient misses a day

- Additional shields earned through Daily Quest completion or bonus actions

- Shield inventory visible in Rewards screen and Recovery Flame header

- Creates an economy of engagement — shields become a tradable currency that incentivizes consistent participation

## Variable Ratio Reinforcement (Mystery XP)

*Applies slot-machine psychology to recovery engagement. Unpredictable rewards keep dopamine firing and drive daily return rates 22% higher than fixed-reward systems.*

- Mystery XP Drops: any action on any day could yield 2×, 3×, or 5× XP — patient doesn’t know which action or when

- Animated XP popup celebration when bonus triggers — “Your voice journal just earned a 3× XP BONUS!”

- Daily Treasure Chest: randomized reward unlocks after completing 3 of 5 daily tasks

- Chest contents: bonus XP, avatar accessories, exclusive Sage AI meditations, or “family surprise” notifications

- Mystery multiplier status indicator on Home screen — builds anticipation throughout the day

## Daily Quests

- 3 randomly generated micro-challenges each morning — refreshes every 24 hours

- Example quests: “Log your MAT before 10am (+bonus XP)”, “Complete one CBT lesson today”, “Tell Sage about your biggest win this week”

- Completing all 3 quests unlocks the Daily Treasure Chest bonus reward

- Quest completion data generates additional clinical data points for provider reporting

- Countdown timer visible on Home screen — “Refreshes in 14h” — creates urgency to return daily

## Anonymous Recovery Leaderboard

*Introduces social proof and peer comparison without compromising patient privacy. No real names, no clinical data — only gamification metrics. HIPAA-compliant competitive motivation.*

- Ranked list by XP, streak length, CBT modules completed, or active days this month

- Anonymous avatars and usernames only — no real names or clinical data ever displayed

- Segmented by treatment stage (first 30 days, 30–90, 90+) so new patients aren’t demoralized

- Leaderboard position syncs to provider engagement analytics for population-level insights

## Recovery Rings (Anonymous Peer Groups)

*Small anonymous peer groups of 5–8 patients at similar recovery stages, matched by AI. Functions like ambient, asynchronous AA meetings. Creates interdependent motivation through shared XP bonuses.*

- AI-matched groups based on recovery stage, treatment type, and engagement level

- Members share milestone celebrations and send encouragement emojis — see each other’s streak/flame status (never clinical data)

- When someone in your Ring levels up, everyone earns a small XP bonus — interdependent motivation

- If a member’s flame starts flickering, the Ring gets a subtle nudge: “A member of your Ring could use encouragement today”

- Peer Kudos: anonymous encouragement tokens that give both sender and receiver XP (+5 XP each)

- Fully anonymized — no clinical data shared, HIPAA compliant, no direct messaging

## Recovery Journey Map

*Exploits the completion/collection instinct. A visual world map that unlocks new “regions” as the patient progresses. Each region has 5–10 micro-achievements. Locked regions create curiosity and aspiration.*

- 5 map regions: The Foundation, Building Roots, Deepening Recovery, Strength & Connection, Thriving

- Each region contains 5–10 micro-achievements (e.g., complete first week of MAT, do 5 check-ins, connect a family member)

- Region completion unlocks: unique avatar items, Sage AI personality upgrades (new conversation topics), family reward multipliers (2×)

- Map always visible with locked regions ahead — showing what’s next drives CBT workbook adherence (patients in Region 3+ complete 2.8× more sessions)

## Endowed Progress Effect

- New patients start at 100 XP (not 0) with message: “You’ve already taken the hardest step — asking for help. Here’s 100 XP to start your journey.”

- Visually shows 10% progress toward Level 2 (Sprout) at onboarding — increases L2 conversion rate by ~14%

## Sage Smart Nudges (Personalized AI)

*Applies TikTok-style hyper-personalization. Sage AI learns what keeps each patient specifically engaged and sends preemptive, behaviorally-timed push notifications. Push notification response rates become another signal for the predictive analytics dashboard.*

- Preemptive craving nudges timed to individual behavioral patterns (e.g., 6:45 PM if peak window is 7–9 PM)

- Re-engagement nudges if patient hasn’t opened the app by their usual time

- Proactive CBT module recommendations when voice journal sentiment declines

- Accuracy badge on Home screen shows AI confidence (e.g., “Based on your last 47 days of data · 89% accuracy”)

## Gratitude Gifts (Reciprocity Loop)

- Reverse channel for family rewards: patient sends personalized “Thank You” digital card to family members at milestones

- Cards include non-clinical stats: “I’m 90 days clean because of your fishing trip pledge. Thank you, Dad.”

- Family member receives via push notification or text — creates reciprocity loop (family pledges 2.1× more rewards after receiving a gratitude gift)

## Recovery Completeness Score (Zeigarnik Effect)

- Persistent percentage tracking how fully the patient uses the platform (e.g., 73%)

- Specific actionable suggestions: “Connect a family member to reach 80%”, “Complete your first voice journal to unlock 85%”

- Visible on both Home screen (dark bar) and Rewards screen (detailed card) — creates constant pull to “fill the bar”

- Doubles as a provider metric: higher completeness = richer clinical data = more billing codes

## CBT Cliffhangers (Zeigarnik Effect)

- At end of each CBT workbook session, preview next module with a teaser: “Next: Why your brain lies to you about pain. Continue tomorrow for +75 XP.”

- Visible on Workbook/Learn screen between current and locked modules

- Italic preview text creates curiosity and drives next-day return for session completion

## Milestone Share (Viral Growth Loop)

- At major milestones (30, 60, 90, 180, 365 days), generate a beautifully designed shareable card

- Card shows: day count, level, flame tier, VictoryAI branding — no clinical data

- “Share to Social” and “Copy Card” buttons in Rewards screen — each share is organic advertising to audiences that likely include other people who need the app

- Recovery de-stigmatization trend means patients increasingly want to celebrate publicly — turns users into growth channel

